# Linguist configuration — keep the repo classified as majority SQL.
#
# Verified (issue #17): GitHub reports the repository as 100% SQL.
#   SQL 30819 bytes | Markdown 9720 | YAML 950
#
# DO NOT DELETE THIS FILE. In Linguist, SQL is `type: data` (like YAML and JSON),
# and data languages are excluded from the language bar by default. The
# linguist-detectable rule below is what makes SQL count at all. Without this
# file the bar would be EMPTY: SQL and YAML are data, Markdown is prose, and all
# three are skipped by default.
#
# The documentation rules are the only optional part: Markdown is already
# excluded as prose, so they merely make the intent explicit. Nothing containing
# real code is hidden from the statistics — even counting every byte of every
# file, SQL is 74.3% of the repository.

# Ensure SQL is always detected and counted.
*.sql linguist-detectable=true
*.sql linguist-language=SQL

# Ancillary / non-source files should not skew the language stats.
docs/**      linguist-documentation
*.md         linguist-documentation

# Normalize line endings.
* text=auto eol=lf
